./observer/logs/reviewer_iter-2_20260620T065454Z.log:457:**`release()` safety**: Only unlock+unlink when the project is tracked in `_fds` (we acquired it). Never unlink a lock file we didn't create. The fd dict is the authoritative ownership record — no PID-match check needed.
./observer/logs/reviewer_iter-2_20260620T065454Z.log:459:**`is_locked()` hybrid check**: On fcntl platforms, try flock first; if it fails the lock is held. If flock succeeds (release immediately), fall back to PID check for backward compat with old-style locks.
./observer/logs/reviewer_iter-2_20260620T065454Z.log:467:With `flock`, stale locks are eliminated: the kernel releases the lock on process exit. The PID-in-file becomes metadata for diagnostics and backward compatibility only.
./observer/logs/reviewer_iter-2_20260620T065454Z.log:472:- `release()` only acts on projects tracked in `_fds`; never touches foreign lock files.
