./observer/logs/reviewer_iter-1_20260620T070243Z.log:1566:./observer/logs/reviewer_iter-2_20260620T065454Z.log:1547:I’m going to record this as `REQUEST_CHANGES`: the revised plan fixed the earlier ownership check, but the proposed `release()` sequence unlocks before removing the path, which reopens the same unlinked-lock race it is trying to avoid.
./observer/logs/reviewer_iter-1_20260620T070243Z.log:1567:./observer/logs/reviewer_iter-2_20260620T065454Z.log:1561:+  - "prd/tech-design.md:89: release() unlocks and closes the fd before unlinking the lock path. After LOCK_UN/os.close and before unlink, another process can open the same path, acquire the flock, write its PID, and then this release() call unlinks that other process's active lock file. The design should keep ownership of the path while removing it, e.g. unlink while still holding the flock and only then unlock/close, so a release cannot delete a successor's lock."
