./observer/logs/reviewer_iter-1_20260620T070243Z.log:1710:./observer/logs/planner_iter-2_20260620T065333Z.log:401:### Review Finding 2 — Fixed: `release()` only touches locks we own
./observer/logs/reviewer_iter-1_20260620T070243Z.log:1711:./observer/logs/planner_iter-2_20260620T065333Z.log:403:**Problem**: Proposed `release()` unconditionally unlinked the lock file even when `project` wasn't in `_fds`, meaning calling `release("nonexistent")` could delete another process's lock file. On flock platforms this is particularly dangerous: the old process's lock stays on the orphaned inode while a new process creates + locks a fresh file at the same path.
