./observer/logs/reviewer_iter-1_20260620T070243Z.log:1834:./reviews/code-review-codex.md:74:### L2: `release()` lacks PID ownership verification (L1)
./observer/logs/reviewer_iter-1_20260620T070243Z.log:1835:./reviews/code-review-codex.md:76:- **Description:** `release()` unconditionally deletes the lock file without verifying that the current process owns it. If a stale lock is overridden by process A, process B (which originally held the lock) could release it later, removing A's lock. This becomes exploitable when combined with the TOCTOU race in `acquire()`.
./observer/logs/reviewer_iter-1_20260620T070243Z.log:1836:./reviews/code-review-codex.md:77:- **Suggested Fix:** On `release()`, read the lock file and only delete if the PID matches `os.getpid()`.
