./observer/logs/reviewer_iter-1_20260620T070243Z.log:2195:+  - "src/unison/lock.py:96-110 and src/unison/lock.py:142-153 catch only BlockingIOError around flock(..., LOCK_NB); Python documents non-blocking flock failure as OSError with errno EACCES or EAGAIN. Any non-BlockingIOError after os.open falls into the outer OSError handler without closing fd. In acquire(), that can leak descriptors and can leave a lock held if the failure happens after flock succeeds but before _fds is updated; in is_locked(), EACCES contention can fall through to the PID fallback and report unlocked for a flock-only holder. Catch OSError around flock, treat EACCES/EAGAIN/EWOULDBLOCK as contention, and close/unlock in finally on every unsuccessful path."
